<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF207-150-084  </DOCNO><DOCID>07 150 084.andM;</DOCID><JOURNAL>PC Week  April 3 1989 v6 n13 p72(1)* Full Text COPYRIGHT Ziff-Davis Publishing Co. 1989.andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Excess inventory makes Aldus latest victim of industry downturn.andO;</TITLE><AUTHOR>March, Richard.andM;</AUTHOR><DESCRIPT>Company:   Aldus Corp. (inventory control).andO;Ticker:    ALDC.andO;Topic:     StockInventory Evaluation.andO;Feature:   illustrationgraphtable.andO;Caption:   PC Week index. (graph)IBM stock: Dow Jones index. (graph)PC Week hardware and software index. (table)andM;</DESCRIPT><TEXT>The specter of excess inventory continues to haunt the PC industry.andP;  AldusCorp.'s stock was last week's victim.andM;In a good news/bad news announcement, officials for the Seattledesktop-publishing-software firm said it will meet securities analysts'estimates of $21.5 million to $22.5 million for first-quarter revenue.andP;  ButAldus officials also said the firm expects second-quarter revenue to be flatbecause of an inventory buildup among distributors.andP;  Officials anticipateflat third-quarter revenue as well.andM;''We are aware that the industry as a whole is experiencing inventorybuildups in the distribution channel,'' said Aldus President Paul Brainerd.andO;''We are continuing to review our inventory levels and sell-through rates inthe channel.''andM;News of the inventory woes triggered a sell-off.andP;  The per-share price ofAldus stock fell from $19 to $16 on March 29 on volume of 1 million shares,about 10 times the average daily volume.andM;In light of the news, analyst Christopher Mortenson of Alex.andP;  Brown andamp; SonsInc., a Baltimore investment bank, lowered his 1989 earnings estimate to$1.37 per share from $1.45.andP;  First-quarter revenue for Aldus a year ago was$15.9 million.andP;  Earnings were $3.1 million.andP;  Inventory problems arose lastyear among chip, disk-drive and some PC manufacturers.andP;  Software giantMicrosoft Corp. reported inventory trouble last month.andP;  -- Richard March</TEXT></DOC>